  - TOKEN_USAGE: Prompt=31828, Gen=424
  - STATE_UPDATE: {'commit_analysis_result': 'The commit analysis has been completed successfully. Let me summarize the findings.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Commit Analysis Completed.**\n\n**Suspect Commit:** `4bce40b3a56501cbae15db44808ccdb25143673f` - "cert-manager: fix broken build (#14036)"\n\n**Why this commit introduced the build error:**\n\n1. **Removed custom Go version pinning**: The previous Dockerfile explicitly downloaded Go 1.24.0 and installed it. This commit removed that, making the build rely on whatever Go version is in the base image (`gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder-go`).\n\n2. **Removed custom `go-118-fuzz-build`**: The previous build.sh cloned a custom fork of `go-118-fuzz-build` and used it. This commit removed that, switching to the built-in `compile_native_go_fuzzer_v2` which uses the system\'s `go-118-fuzz-build`.\n\n3. **The incompatibility**: The base image (at the used digest) ships with Go 1.25.7, which stores the toolchain under `GOMODCACHE` (`/root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64/`). The `go-118-fuzz-build` tool creates an overlay JSON that replaces `testing/fuzz.go`, but Go 1.25+ **forbids overlay replacements under GOMODCACHE**, causing the build to fail with:\n   ```\n   go: overlay contains a replacement for /root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64/src/testing/fuzz.go. Files beneath GOMODCACHE (/root/go/pkg/mod) must not be replaced.\n   ```\n\nThe fix would need to either pin an older Go version or update the `go-118-fuzz-build` overlay mechanism to be compatible with Go 1.25+.'}
